comments: Quickley (NYK) re-establishes in Nwora's (MIL) path and initiates contact that affects Nwora's ability to defend around the screen.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in Barrett's (NYK) path and absorbs the contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) brings his left hand toward Gibson's (NYK) back and marginal contact occurs as Antetokounmpo slows his forward momentum to change direction.
Gibson (NYK) extends his hand forward and marginal contact occurs with Lopez's (MIL) front during the dunk attempt.

Antetokounmpo (MIL) extends his left arm outward and some contact occurs with Quickley's (NYK) head/neck area as Quickley is cutting. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Connaughton (MIL) has his left hand positioned forward when marginal contact occurs with Rose's (NYK) front at the end of the drive.
Rose's (NYK) right arm extends toward Connaughton (MIL) as Rose attempts to bring both hands to the ball and marginal contact occurs.
Rose (NYK) legally re-gains possession of the ball after fumbling it at the end of the drive.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) has his right hand extended forward when he brushes Rose's (NYK) right arm as Rose is passing.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in Barrett's (NYK) path and gives Barrett room to avoid the contact, which Lopez absorbs.
Gibson (NYK) reaches in and initiates contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) left arm, affecting Antetokounmpo's SQBR.
Lopez (MIL) has his forearm rested on Barrett's (NYK) back and marginal contact occurs as Lopez back-taps the rebound.
Lopez (MIL) moves toward Burks (NYK) and marginal body contact occurs in the front-court.
Lopez (MIL) has his right hand extended forward when marginal contact occurs with Barrett's (NYK) left shoulder at the start of Barrett's dribble.
Barrett (NYK) cleanly dislodges Antetokounmpo (MIL) of the ball in transition.
Gibson (NYK) and Lopez (MIL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Gibson (NYK) moves into Lopez's (MIL) space and initiates contact that affects Lopez's SQBR. The contact occurs prior to and causes any potential traveling violation by Lopez.
Rose (NYK) and Forbes (MIL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Lopez (MIL) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
Gibson (NYK) is moving toward Lopez (MIL) and marginal contact occurs to Lopez's backside as he receives the pass.
Rose (NYK) legally contests Forbes' (MIL) jump shot attempt and would avoid Forbes' right foot if he didn't extend it forward to initiate the marginal contact.
Burks (NYK) has his hand rested on Connaughton's (MIL) back and marginal contact occurs as Burks releases away to retrieve the rebound.
Quickley (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Connaughton's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact.
Connaughton (MIL) attempts to commit a take foul on Quickley (NYK) and the contact is marginal.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.

Replay review of the foul called on Lopez (MIL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Lopez (MIL) initiates contact with Burks' (NYK) arms and causes him to lose control of the ball during rebounding.
NYK is awarded the timeout prior to Nwora (MIL) or Antetokounmpo (MIL) tying up or fouling Quickley (NYK).
Antetokounmpo (MIL) initiates contact with Barrett's (NYK) back/arm prior to making any contact with the ball.
